# Marketing Content

## Brand and Voice

- Follow **brand voice guidelines** consistently across all channels.
- Maintain a consistent tone that aligns with brand positioning.
- Use approved terminology and messaging frameworks.

## Calls to Action

- Include a **clear CTA** in every piece of content. The reader should always know what to do next.
- Make CTAs specific and action-oriented: "Download the 2026 Report" not "Learn more."

## SEO Best Practices

- Place the **target keyword** in the title, H1, and first paragraph.
- Use semantic variations of the keyword throughout the body.
- Write meta descriptions under 160 characters with the target keyword.
- Use descriptive, keyword-rich URLs.

## Social Media

- Follow **platform-specific** length and format guidelines:
  - LinkedIn: 1,300 characters max for organic posts; professional tone.
  - X/Twitter: 280 characters; concise and punchy.
  - Instagram: visual-first; captions under 2,200 characters.
- Adapt content for each platform rather than cross-posting identical copy.

## Content Integrity

- **All claims must be substantiated** with data, sources, or references.
- Include **alt text** for all images describing the content and context.
- Attribute quotes, statistics, and research to their original source.

## Testing and Optimization

- **A/B test headlines** when possible to optimize engagement.
- Track performance metrics relevant to the content goal (clicks, conversions, shares).
- Review and update evergreen content on a regular schedule.

## Checklist

- [ ] Brand voice and tone consistent
- [ ] Clear CTA present
- [ ] Target keyword in title, H1, and first paragraph
- [ ] All claims substantiated
- [ ] Alt text on all images
- [ ] Platform-appropriate format and length
